What the package contains:

SECTION 1 — Representative photo policy
Hard rule: nothing gets called a JAG project photo unless Toby supplies it. Stock, AI-generated, and designed assets all have distinct labeling rules. The honest record lives in alt text and the source inventory — no ugly on-screen "stock photo" badges that undermine the site's premium feel.

SECTION 2 — 28 photo slots across every route
Every slot has: Slot ID, route, section, exact visual direction, aspect ratio, alt text, source type, and priority (CRITICAL / HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW). The six service page heroes are all CRITICAL. The about page Joe Gendre photo is flagged as the single highest-ROI image on the entire site.

SECTION 3 — 7 Rex prompts (optional)
Ready to run if Toby approves AI-generated representative images. Each prompt is tight and electrical-trade-specific. QC rules for rejecting garbled AI output are included.

SECTION 4 — Photo-to-motion clips (no Hyperframes required)
A single FFmpeg zoompan recipe that turns any sourced hero photo into a 15-second Ken Burns background clip for each service page. Low effort, high perceived quality. All 6 service filenames listed. Embed spec included so Craig can drop it in without guessing.

SECTION 5 — Master alt text table
One row per slot, ready to paste into code. City page alt text is honest location description, not "representative image," because those are actual photos of the named city.

SECTION 6 — Source inventory template
Forge logs every sourced image here with URL, license, and status. QUARANTINED status is included — if Toby rejects a photo it is locked out with reason, not silently substituted.

SECTION 7 — QC rules (mechanical + visual + claims gate)
Three tiers: automated checks Forge can run, visual checks Eddie reviews before approval, and the truth-boundary claims gate that ensures no caption invents a project or violates the fact brief.

SECTION 8 — Toby decisions that unblock slots
Joe Gendre's headshot for /about is Priority 1. Rex approval is Priority 1. City photo sourcing strategy is Priority 2.

SECTIONS 9–11 — Cross-references, sequencing order, Chad handoff gate
Forge knows what order to work. Chad knows not to run paid ads until Toby approves.
